entries.value: A strange little creature is exactly what Orglyn is. Known as the brightest one on Jewel Paradise, this monster plays a sweet organ sounding... Thingy. They have a special organ (no pun intended) just for making the sound.
Triturtouds help keep the world hydrated. A curious creature, its three eyes peek around as it plays its sound. Friendly and dreamy.

A QlariQ'ill could Q'ill you, so be careful! This Chromatic Monster has spikes sharper than a razor, though a carefully played song seems to calm its jagged thorns and keep its focus on the rhythm instead of harm. Some Monsters believe QlariQ'ill can see the future of a melody before it's ever played... others think it simply reacts very quickly.

Once a simple worker, GeahrHeed became part of the machinery itself. Every twist of his body tightens the factory's loop, ensuring nothing ever runs loose, except, perhaps, the minds of those who listen too closely.
A tiny creature that wanders the factory with confident steps. It plays its sound by spinning its body like a crank. The longer it plays, the colder the factory feels...

A curious creature born from frozen currency and factory treats, P'opsiccelle produces its cheerful chimes by violently shaking itself. Despite its playful sound, it takes its job seriously, as value doesn't circulate unless it's heard.

The Fruicca are quite the hard-to-spot specimen due to their environment being found mostly in the deepest depths of the Monster World's oceans. They are quite the bubbly and bright monsters, that second statement being both figuratively and literally! The Fruicca's four tentacles(?) emit a bioluminescent glow, which they use to light up the darkened abyss of which they reside and to produce their unique song. Along with bioluminescent tentacles, they have developed four eyes of varying sizes for a much greater field of view. Talk about four eyes... literally!

Hollon! What do you think you're doing?
Thats what I thought.
This monster is a peace keeper, making sure everyone and everything is in the right place at the right time, and making sure no trouble is caused.
Friage chills the factory to unbearable temperatures, sealing its doors and sounds. When its doors shut, a deep pounding fills the air, but when they open, frozen harmony thaws out.

Vyrdiits have a unique story. They weren't born to be a singer, their song is actually them breathing! They have special fibers in their breathing tubes that unknowingly transform it into a melody, even if it's just trying to survive. They seem to be pretty grumpy from all the other loud noises, so maybe you should make them happy by muting every other monster?

Before we explain anything else, just note this: Do NOT seperate Sprimba from its little buddy. Okay? Anyways, Sprimbas love to be in water and swim, so much as to make it their forever home! They don't have much that belongs to them, except their little sticks, little buddy and the little rocks that surround it, so their little sticks can make a little noise by tapping the little rocks.

As the owner of his factory, Jehyre takes several precautions to prevent anyone from harming him, as he is most vulnerable while singing. This is why he remains hidden behind a mask. Some say that if you were to see his true self... you would pass out.

Flohr-Tri keeps perfect time within the factory, endlessly ticking away as if counting something long forgotten. It's believed she originated from the final moments of Floor Two, trapped in an eternal loop where every second is louder than the last.

Found mostly on the second floor of Jehyre's Factory, the Rare P'opsiccelle is known for tasting quite... disgusting. It is theorized this is because it sits on the greasy oil stained floors 24/7, though we aren't quite sure.
A solid foundation of rhythm, oOdu is the heartbeat of any island! With a sturdy head and a thumping beat, it keeps the music going strong.

Shubudop! Sappots are known as the "Most healthy monster", as they make their own food, you see the soil in their head? Every summer, they plant 5-10 seeds in there, and by fall, it grows into huge trees with very nutricious fruit. Though for the rest of the year, they plant some wheat in there as snacks just in case.
Dewdish prefers to let its voice do the floating. This singer glides into the song with its simple voice. Without Dewdish, the song might just feel a little dry.

The starter of all Key elementals. Evolving from having eyes on their mouths, one thing you may not know about this monster is that it has perfect hygiene! You may think how without any arms, but with the help with a bopells floating hand it can have the best teeth cleaning in the entire island!
With a body as tough as stone and a heart as steady as a drum, Bouldin provides a deep, resonant whistle that calms the air. Though its expression is stoic, its beats are full of energy and life!

In a newly discovered world, sometimes you have to cut corners. That's why Didgeridoo is named after its instrument. Originally being unable to fly, in case of an emergency, Didgeridoos have evolved to have flying wings!

Blank Monsters are quite unique, most in part for being the mother(?) of nearly every monster, assuming you don't purchase them from the shop. They don't have consciousness like most monsters, but they change the song more than you think! Don't worry, they are perfectly fine about it!

A WaaVox is just what you need to bring an island to life. This energetic monster seems to always have a wet hand, we aren't sure where the water comes from, but it helps smooth out its instrument when playing. It must have its head held high for the sound to be released from its mouth, or else it might explode!


that actually happened once

rest in peace

Bopells are peaceful creatures who avoid conflict, preferring instead to chime their bells in harmony. They are formed through a mystical process, where stone is carved into shape and infused with magic to bring them to life.

Wamphybs love to be wowed. Though, they hate to be alone. Studies show they sometimes start singing to themselves, hoping someone will join in and share the excitement, though they can get easily distracted, disrupting the islands song.

You may be confused during your endeavures, hearing a choir, but seeing none in sight. But thats when you stumble upon this little bird called Flocket! It uses its throat to harmonize with itself; its long neck has 3 sets of vocal chords, allowing it to make more than one sound at a time, like a choir!
